    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-11-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="127" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-11-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 17,
                            1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President is anxious that an agreement should speedily be reached for
                        carrying out the decision and recommendations of the Paris Tribunal. If Lord
                        Rosebery has met you in a proper spirit we do not doubt results. Are you
                        hopeful?</p>
            </div>
